criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Aged 40-75 years;

          -  Patients with first-onset subcortical infarcts in the dominant hemisphere with onset
             of 1 to 3 weeks;

          -  TMS on the lesion side can induce motor evoked potential(MEP) of the abductor pollicis
             brevis muscle of the affected hand;

          -  Consciousness, sitting balance level 1 or above, can cooperate with assessment and
             treatment;

          -  The patient or its authorized agent signs the informed consent form.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Previous seizures;

          -  Suffered from mental illness such as depression, anxiety, mania, and schizophrenia
             before the stroke onset;

          -  Patients with metal on the head, cochlear implants, intracranial infections, etc. who
             are not suitable for rTMS.
